<br>
1) The government sits in private sessions for months working on new bills LONG before it is public knowledge. Why you ask. If they didn't do it this way, well we would still be in the bronze age trying to figure out how to make stronger metals.Once they have the bills the way they like them they then take them to congress/senate to be voted on, the MILLIONS of people in the country do not get a say it this voting. Period. Over time a few things do get changed but not alot, same as what goes on with the RTA.<br>
<br>
2) The owner of a company announces that there will be lay-offs due to financial problems. Are you mad about this? Yes. Do you goto him and ask if you can see the company record, so you can see this for yourself? No.<br>
Why? Because it has nothing to do with you because you are not in a high enough position in the company to see such documentation. Do you tell the owner that you have the &quot;right&quot; to see them? No, because you do NOT have that right.<br>
<br>
Now if after this you still don't understand, i suggest you go back to school and start right off at kindergarten again, because i do not think this can be made anymore clear that how i have laid this out for you. It time you realize there are things in this world you do not know about wether it be RL issues or game issues, this is how the world works and has worked for thousands of years. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rigorre>Rigorre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/16/03 8:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1) The government sits in private sessions for months working on new bills LONG before it is public knowledge. Why you ask. If they didn't do it this way, well we would still be in the bronze age trying to figure out how to make stronger metals.Once they have the bills the way they like them they then take them to congress/senate to be voted on, the MILLIONS of people in the country do not get a say it this voting. Period. Over time a few things do get changed but not alot, same as what goes on with the RTA.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You are wrong.  The government does not 'sit in private sessions' ...limited attendance, perhaps ...but certainly not 'private'.  (At least, not here in the United States, and I do concede that not everyone lives in the United States ...however, I also contend that not many live in Communist China either).  Media is allowed to attend if they so desire.  The conversations of those 'sessions' are transcripted and are a matter of public record.<br>
<br>
This is an important point, so read slowly ...Most importantly, I am represented before any bill is ever signed into law.  Someone who *I* have chosen has been either actively involved or privy to the information that the bill is based on.<br>
<br>
Therein lies the fundamental flaw of the RTA government.  There is no 'senate' ...there is no 'congress' ...there is no representation of the entire community before a 'rotation bill' is introduced 'behind closed doors' ...and a 'rotation law' is passed, again 'behind closed doors'.  You say it does not affect 'the entire community outside of the Elemental Planes' ...and I say, &quot;YES IT DOES&quot;.  I may not know what a &quot;ButtThumper&quot; is in the Plane of Fire ...nor can anyone not in the Plane of Fire offer any relevant information on it ...but to say that a law governing the access to a &quot;ButtThumper&quot; in the Plane of Fire does not affect me is ridiculous.  Go back and read my example of patmcrotch and his sheep screwing again.<br>
<br>
Granting the RTA Guild Representatives READ ONLY access to the Elemental Planes forum would, in essence, create a kind of 'senate', and I for one would be completely happy with that.  It is not the perfect solution ...in a perfect world, our 'senate' would have input (the ability to post to that forum, ask questions, and offer suggestions for changes) ...but I am willing to concede that point in the interest of fairness to the top 10% and their belief that anyone not in the Elem Planes lacks the technical information needed to make an informed opinion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2) The owner of a company announces that there will be lay-offs due to financial problems. Are you mad about this? Yes. Do you goto him and ask if you can see the company record, so you can see this for yourself? No.<br>
Why? Because it has nothing to do with you because you are not in a high enough position in the company to see such documentation. Do you tell the owner that you have the &quot;right&quot; to see them? No, because you do NOT have that right.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You are exactly right on this point.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, the RTA neither presents itself as a private corporation, nor can it ever present itself as a private corporation because they do not OWN the world of Everquest or the Everquest server, The Rathe.  The primary difference between government (a public 'corporation') and Microsoft (a private corporation) can be ascertained in exactly one point:  Ownership.<br>
<br>
The RTA does not OWN anything.  The top 10% of the RTA does not OWN anything.  ...and no, possession in this case does not represent ownership.  Neither the RTA or the top 10% can declare 'ownership' (and thereby declare private corporation law) because they do not control the existance of that content.  If I 'own' something, I am allowed to destroy it, correct?<br>
<br>
SOE owns it ...they make the rules ...they make the laws we live by ...and as a private corporation who OWNS it, they are perfectly within their rights to do so.  As Elemental Planes capable guilds, do you think you have the 'right' to go make demands of SOE?<br>
<br>
So, you do not own it, you cannot be protected by private corporate law.  The RTA is a government and falls clearly in your first point and my counterpoint.<br>
